This paper is primarily focused on network topology discovery, which falls under the category of computer networks and internet architecture (cs.NI). The paper also discusses the potential security implications of active probing, which could place it in the category of cryptography and security (cs.CR). Additionally, the paper discusses the scalability and parallelism of the proposed technique, which could place it in the categories of distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC), social and information networks (cs.SI), and information theory (cs.IT).
